  "prompt": "How do you deal with a jealous backstabbing co-worker?",
  "response": "Here are some strategies for dealing with a jealous or backstabbing co-worker:\n\n1. Stay professional\n- Don't engage in gossip or negative behavior\n- Keep interactions cordial and work-focused\n- Document any inappropriate actions\n\n2. Maintain boundaries\n- Be polite but limit personal interactions\n- Don't share sensitive personal information\n- Keep communication strictly work-related\n\n3. Build strong work relationships\n- Network with other colleagues\n- Demonstrate your value through your work performance\n- Maintain a positive reputation\n\n4. Address issues directly if necessary\n- Have a calm, private conversation with the co-worker\n- Express concerns about specific behaviors\n- Focus on work-related issues, not personal attacks\n\n5. Protect yourself\n- Save emails and documentation\n- Be aware of potential undermining tactics\n- Report serious issues to HR if needed\n\n6. Focus on your own performance\n- Don't let their behavior distract you\n- Continue to do excellent work\n- Stay confident in your abilities\n\n7. Consider long-term strategies\n- If situation doesn't improve, explore transfer or new job options\n- Seek advice from mentor or supervisor if needed\n\nRemember to remain calm, professional, and focused on your work throughout the process.",
